    "type": "substream",
    "extraDescription": "Labor and employment law focuses on the relationship between employers and employees, covering issues such as wage disputes, worker\u2019s compensation, workplace safety, and wrongful termination. It also encompasses anti-discrimination laws, union negotiations, and employee benefits. Lawyers in this field protect workers' rights while ensuring employers follow labor regulations, preventing unfair treatment. Employment law is crucial for establishing fair working conditions, regulating workplace disputes, and enforcing legal protections for workers in various industries.",
