  "data": {
    "streamId": "stream_2_578a9a2c-7039-4746-b2aa-10a207d47286",
    "substream_Name": " Textile Design",
    "description": "Textile design focuses on creating fabrics, patterns, and textures. It plays a critical role in the fashion industry. Textile designers bring innovation to materials.",
    "imageurl": "https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.qcPV4O-HwKyi-HqtiChw-QHaFg?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain",
    "type": "substream",
    "extraDescription": "Textile design is a highly technical and creative field that goes hand-in-hand with fashion design. Designers in this substream focus on fabric construction, surface patterns, and textures that define how garments look and feel. By experimenting with dyes, weaving, knitting, and printing techniques, textile designers create unique fabric designs that influence entire fashion collections. The development of innovative fabrics, such as eco-friendly textiles or high-tech fabrics used for performance wear, has dramatically transformed how we approach fashion. A textile designer\u2019s work ensures that the fabric used in garments not only looks good but also serves the purpose it was created for\u2014whether it's durability, breathability, or comfort.",
