    "substream_Name": "Accessory Design",
    "description": "Involves designing fashion accessories like jewelry, bags, and hats. Accessories enhance an outfit's style. They can be functional and fashionable.",
    "imageurl": "https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.MIECAn8Lmkz0mqTQlnw0yAHaE7?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain",
    "type": "substream",
    "extraDescription": "Accessory design adds a creative touch to any outfit by focusing on smaller fashion pieces that complete the overall look. This substream includes creating functional and ornamental accessories like handbags, belts, scarves, jewelry, and even headwear. Designers experiment with various materials, from metals and gemstones in jewelry to leather, fabric, and synthetic materials in handbags. The role of an accessory designer goes beyond just creating visually appealing pieces; they must understand how accessories influence style and outfit coordination. Accessories often serve as statements of individuality, and their design can significantly impact fashion trends. Designers are increasingly combining technology with accessories, producing smart jewelry or bags with integrated features.",
    "extraImageUrl": "https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.MIECAn8Lmkz0mqTQlnw0yAHaE7?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain",
